y to assist you with both service and general information relating to your garage door or opener unit.";i:17;s:70:"We are recipients of Angies List SUPER SERVICE AWARD and BEST OF HOME.";i:18;s:138:"To adjust your garage doors side-mounted springs first open your door fully and secure it in place with a c-clamp below the bottom roller.";i:19;s:147:"Once your garage door is secured remove the spring hook from the track hanger which will allow you to move the hook and adjust the springs tension.";i:20;s:33:"How to adjust the overhead track.";i:21;s:111:"Check out that the overhead part of the track and the wall track are at the same distance from the garage door.";i:22;s:62:"If you notice any difference lower the door and start working.";i:23;s:102:"You need to relocate the end of the track so that it is parallel with the door 05 to 075 away from it.";i:24;s:133:"If your door doesnt rise at least five feet when it is suppose to be opening hold the bottom of the garage door while it is lowering.";i:25;s:32:"This will adjust the open force.";i:26;s:96:"For a door that doesnt reverse while closing hold the door as it opens to adjust the down force.";i:27;s:35:"Step 3 - Adjust the Safety Reverse.";i:28;s:152:"Up and over garage doors operate by running along a series of tracks which must be properly aligned so the door moves flawlessly as it opens and closes.";i:29;s:157:"If the garage door opener is not adjusted properly there is a risk that the door will run along the track unevenly causing it to become lodged in the tracks.";i:30;s:31:"If Your Garage Door is Binding.";i:31;s:60:"Here are the steps to follow if your garage door is binding.";i:32;s:85:"Using a screwdriver loosen the screws which hold the tracks in the garage door frame.";i:33;s:105:"Now you can align the track so it is perfectly vertical by tapping it at the bottom with a rubber mallet.";i:34;s:24:"Odyssey 1000 Model 7030.";i:35;s:82:"Learn how to program the Overhead Door Odyssey 1000 Model 7030 garage door opener.";i:36;s:131:"An overhead garage door is a large heavy object and in order for it to operate properly it must be precisely balanced and adjusted.";i:37;s:60:"Several parts of the door mechanism are prone to adjustment.";i:38;s:71:"I began learning the garage door trade in the Chicago blizzard of 1979.";i:39;s:62:"One of the more challenging jobs was replacing four huge 6 ID.";i:40;s:65:"Torsion springs on large 22 X 14 sectional overhead garage doors.";i:41;s:88:"These instructions are for 4 - 6 torsion springs with center-mount operator inside lift.";i:42;s:148:"Make no mistake changing garage door springs can be dangerous and an overhead door company should be called if the task is out of ones comfort zone.";i:43;s:103:"When winding or unwinding the springs they can snap without warning which can result in serious injury.";i:44;s:37:"Garage Door Spring Replacement Guide.";i:45;s:21:"Shut the garage door.";i:46;s:169:"For an automatic door unplug the opener then place a c-clamp on the track of the garage door to avoid the door opening while you are adjusting the tension in its spring.";i:47;s:24:"Detect the winding cone.";i:48;s:91:"Pinpoint exactly where the spring ends by placing one eye over the stationary center plate.";i:49;s:146:"Tie a string long enough to span the width of the garage door around the bracket on one side so that the string will line up with the sensor lens.";i:50;s:71:"Pull the string taut and tie to the other bracket in the same position.";i:51;s:45:"Using a level check that the string is level.";i:52;s:73:"If not adjust one or both of the sensors to bring the string up to level.";i:53;s:44:"Using the wall button close the garage door.";i:54;s:67:"Locate the curved close limit slot on the back of the opener motor.";i:55;s:93:"Insert a screw driver into the adjustment screw and turn the screw counterclockwise for more.";i:56;s:49:"Close travel and clockwise for less close travel.";i:57;s:50:"Make small adjustments to travel limits at a time.";i:58;s:74:"We deliver high quality Garage Door Track Adjustment Replacement services.";i:59;s:55:"Call 587 804-2072 for 24 hour emergency repair support.";i:60;s:30:"10526 Jasper Ave 202 Edmonton.";i:61;s:93:"A properly adjusted garage door is vital for energy efficiency security and wildlife control.";i:62;s:77:"Garage doors are very easy to adjust and can be done in less than 15 minutes.";i:63;s:93:"Each garage door opener has limits which control the opening and closing heights of the door.";i:64;s:37:"Finding the Height Adjustment Screws.";i:65;s:106:"The height limit adjustment screws of your garage door can be found on the side of the garage door opener.";i:66;s:33:"Most of them are made in plastic.";i:67;s:95:"You will recognize them because they will have markings that say Open and Close or Up and Down.";i:68;s:41:"After finding them move to the next step.";}}